      "id": "CVE-2025-8713",
      "source": "postgresql",
      "title": "PostgreSQL optimizer statistics can expose sampled data within a view, partition, or child table",
      "description": "PostgreSQL optimizer statistics allow a user to read sampled data within a\nview that the user cannot access. Separately, statistics allow a user to read\nsampled data that a row security policy intended to hide. PostgreSQL maintains\nstatistics for tables by sampling data available in columns; this data is\nconsulted during the query planning process. Prior to this release, a user\ncould craft a leaky operator that bypassed view access control lists (ACLs)\nand bypassed row security policies in parti",
      "severity": "low",
      "cvss_score": 3.1,
